AUDIO: 'Welcome back. In this video, we will explore an amazing new comfy UI workflow for advanced character animation using One 2.2 Animate. We will show you how to take a static image and a driving video and perfectly'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'transfer the motion, facial expressions, and poses to your character. Before we dive into the technical details, make sure to check out our website linked in the description below. Our team has created a dedicated hub'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'where you can find all of our workflows, detailed information, and helpful resources. Also, we want to highlight that we are using the Mimic PC platform for this tutorial.'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We provide a fully ready-made template for this workflow, meaning you do not have to worry about manually downloading gigabytes of models or setting up complex environments. You just click the link we provide, select your GPU, and in a few minutes,'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the workflow is completely ready to run. This setup is a powerful character reshaping and motion transfer tool. It uses a combination of advanced AI models to isolate your character, understand'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'their appearance, and map the movements from a source video seamlessly onto them. It is perfect for creating dynamic character animations, making virtual avatars, or turning a simple drawing into a dancing or talking video.'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'At the beginning of the workflow, we have our input section where you upload your reference image and the driving video. The driving video is what dictates the motion. From there, the workflow uses Florence 2 and SAM 2.'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Florence 2 analyzes your image to generate a highly detailed text description, while SAM 2 precisely segments the character from the background. This ensures that only the character gets animated, while preventing'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'background distortion. Next, we extract the motion. We use DWPose and ViTPose alongside YOLO face detection to carefully track the body movements and facial expressions from your driving'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. These precise poses are then translated into a format that the main animation model can understand. The heart of this workflow is the 12.2 animate model. We load this massive 14 billion'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'parameter model alongside crucial memory optimization nodes like block swap and T cache. If you are running this on a GPU with less than 16 GB of V RAM, you will definitely want to ensure the block swap'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'settings are active to prevent out of memory errors. The 1 video animate embeds node is where the real magic happens. It takes the pose data, the face data, the segmented image, and the text prompt blending them'

[02:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all together. For settings you can tweak, pay close attention to the resolution and frame rate switches we have set up. You can easily switch between 480p and 720p for both horizontal and vertical'

[02:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'formats depending on your project needs. Once the sampler processes the frames, the VAE decodes them and the video combine node stitches it all back together with the original audio from'

[03:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your driving video. It is a highly automated pipeline that produces incredible fluid results. Remember, you can find this exact setup on our website and with Mimic PC, you are just a couple'

